---
import Section from "./Section.astro";
import { ShieldCheck } from "lucide-astro";
---

<Section bordered>
	<div class="callout">
		<div class="callout-header">
			<div class="callout-icon">
				<ShieldCheck aria-hidden="true" />
			</div>
			<div>
				<h2 class="callout-title">Determinism contract</h2>
				<p class="callout-tagline">
					Same seed plus same fixed_dt plus same recorded action stream plus same code
					equals byte-identical world hash on every run.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="callout-body">
			This is the engine's hard guarantee and the foundation of replay-as-fixture testing.
			Replay tests are cheap regression coverage — record a winning run once, replay it on
			every CI. Save/load round-trips are bit-exact. Bug repros become "run this 12-second
			JSON against the latest code" instead of "WASD a bunch and see if the player gets stuck".
		</p>

		<div class="callout-grid">
			<div class="callout-cell">
				<div class="callout-cell-label">Guaranteed</div>
				<ul class="callout-list">
					<li>Integer <code>time.tick</code></li>
					<li>Insertion-ordered systems</li>
					<li>Sorted entity iteration</li>
					<li>Seeded mulberry32 RNG</li>
					<li>Action streams over events</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="callout-cell">
				<div class="callout-cell-label">Banned outside <code>src/pixi/</code></div>
				<ul class="callout-list">
					<li><code>Date.now()</code></li>
					<li><code>Math.random()</code></li>
					<li><code>setTimeout</code> / <code>setInterval</code></li>
					<li><code>pixi.js</code> imports</li>
					<li>Async game logic (no <code>await</code> in systems)</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Section>

<style>
	.callout {
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
		background: var(--bg-alt);
		padding: var(--space-lg);
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-md);
	}

	.callout-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-start;
		gap: var(--space-md);
	}

	.callout-icon {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 2rem;
		height: 2rem;
		flex-shrink: 0;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		background: var(--bg);
		color: var(--fg);
	}

	.callout-icon :global(svg) {
		width: 1.125rem;
		height: 1.125rem;
	}

	.callout-title {
		font-size: var(--text-lg);
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--fg);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xs) 0;
	}

	.callout-tagline {
		font-size: var(--text-sm);
		color: var(--fg-muted);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.callout-body {
		font-size: var(--text-base);
		color: var(--fg-muted);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.callout-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: var(--space-md);
	}

	.callout-cell {
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		background: var(--bg);
		padding: var(--space-md);
	}

	.callout-cell-label {
		font-size: var(--text-xs);
		font-weight: 600;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		color: var(--fg-faint);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
	}

	.callout-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-xs);
	}

	.callout-list li {
		font-size: var(--text-sm);
		color: var(--fg-muted);
	}

	.callout-list code,
	.callout-tagline code,
	.callout-body code {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.9em;
		padding: 1px 6px;
		background: var(--bg-alt);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		color: var(--fg);
	}

	.callout-cell .callout-list code {
		background: var(--bg-alt);
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.callout-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.callout-header {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
		}
	}
</style>
